# TB Pro Reports тАФ Sonnet Maintenance Guide

Read **before** editing any TB Pro report HTML or generator script. Also: `tbpro-launch-sample.mdc`, `tbpro-theme-tickets.mdc`, `tbpro-table-patterns.mdc`, `tbpro-copy-tone.mdc`.

## All TB Pro reports тАФ Sonnet maintenance scope

| Report | Sample/live file | Generator | Sonnet-safe when |
|--------|------------------|-----------|------------------|
| Daily Flight 2 | `lisa/daily/latest.html` | `scripts/tbpro_daily.py` | After redesign sample approved (future) |
| Launch overview | `launch_overview_sample.html` тЖТ `launch_overview.html` | `tbpro_launch_overview.py` | Sample in progress / playbook established |
| Weekly | `reports/tbpro/LATEST_WEEKLY.html` | `tbpro_weekly.py` | After daily/launch samples done (`DESIGN.md` scope) |
| Monthly | `lisa/YYYY/month_sample.html` тЖТ `month.html` | `generate.py` | Queued тАФ see `monthly-report-planned.mdc` |

**Principles apply to ALL reports:**

- CSS vars in `:root` only тАФ no raw hex in component rules
- `<!-- SECTION: name -->` comments at major boundaries; edit one section at a time
- Paraphrased PII тАФ never raw Zendesk subjects, emails, names, or ticket bodies
- No `display:flex` on `th`/`td` тАФ use `.tbl-sort__inner` (see `tbpro-table-patterns.mdc`)
- Explicit CSS classes тАФ avoid one-off inline styles
- **Sample gate** before generator тАФ prototype in `*_sample.html`; do not edit live output or Python until Lisa approves
- Read this file + relevant TB Pro rules **before every edit**

